org.apache.river.test.spec.constraint.coreconstraint.util

Class AbstractSimpleTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.qa.harness.QATestEnvironment
      • org.apache.river.test.spec.constraint.coreconstraint.util.AbstractSimpleTest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Test, TestEnvironment
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EqualsTest, HashCodeTest, ToStringTest

    public abstract class AbstractSimpleTest
extends QATestEnvironment
implements Test
    
 This is an auxiliary abstract class.

 This is an auxiliary abstract class to test methods of the following classes:
   TestCase #1:  ClientAuthentication
   TestCase #2:  ClientMaxPrincipal
   TestCase #3:  ClientMaxPrincipalType
   TestCase #4:  ClientMinPrincipal
   TestCase #5:  ClientMinPrincipalType
   TestCase #6:  Confidentiality
   TestCase #7:  ConnectionAbsoluteTime
   TestCase #8:  ConnectionRelativeTime
   TestCase #9:  ConstraintAlternatives
   TestCase #10: Delegation
   TestCase #11: DelegationAbsoluteTime
   TestCase #12: DelegationRelativeTime
   TestCase #13: Integrity
   TestCase #14: InvocationConstraints
   TestCase #15: ServerAuthentication
   TestCase #16: ServerMinPrincipal

 In each Test Case 3 objects of the corresponding type are created:
   - 2 equal objects (obj1.equals(obj2) produces true);
   - object that is different from obj1 and obj2 (obj1.equals(obj3)
     produces false).
 Then in each test case checker(Object, Object, Object) method
 is invoked. Test passes if checker(Object, Object, Object) method
 returns true in each case.

 This class is extended by the following tests:
   ToStringTest
   EqualsTest
   HashCodeTest
 Each of these tests implements checker(Object, Object, Object)
 method according to the assertion to be tested in the test.

      • checker

        public abstract boolean checker(Object primObj,
                                Object equalObj,
                                Object diffObj)
        Abstract method to test objects of the same type. Subclasses override this method to implement specific tests. This method returns true if all conditions/checks of the specific test are satisfied or false otherwise.
        Parameters:
        primObj - the primary object
        equalObj - object that is equal to the primary object
        diffObj - object that isn't equal to the primary object
        Returns:
        true if all conditions of the specific test are satisfied or false otherwise
